## Environment Variables & Multi-Environment Separation

To prevent cross-environment contamination and support local Docker testing without breaking cloud production deployments, environment configuration is split strictly between development and production files:

### Backend Environments (`backend/`)
- **`.env.development`** *(Loaded automatically via `npm run dev` / `ts-node`)*:
  - Points `REDIS_HOST` to `127.0.0.1` / `localhost` (local Docker container running on laptop).
  - Sets `BASE_DOMAIN=localhost` for local domain generation.
- **`.env.production`** *(Loaded automatically via `NODE_ENV=production` / `node dist/server.js` / PM2)*:
  - Points `REDIS_HOST` to live production EC2 Redis daemon (`127.0.0.1` on `13.238.226.195`).
  - Sets `BASE_DOMAIN=microps.in` for live SaaS subdomains.

### Frontend Environments (`frontend/`)
- **`.env.development`** *(Loaded automatically via Vite on `npm run dev`)*:
  - `VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000/api/v1` (points directly to laptop backend).
- **`.env.production`** *(Loaded automatically via Vite on `npm run build`)*:
  - `VITE_API_URL=http://13.238.226.195/api/v1` (points directly to live EC2 Nginx / PM2 API cluster).

| Variable Name | Component | Purpose |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `PORT` | Backend | HTTP server listening port (Default: `8000`) |
| `DATABASE_URL` | Backend | Connection string for Neon Cloud PostgreSQL instance |
| `REDIS_HOST` / `REDIS_PORT`| Backend | Host and port for Redis message broker (`localhost` in dev, EC2 host in prod) |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Backend | Cryptographic secret for signing Bearer authentication tokens |
| `AWS_REGION` | Backend | AWS region for deployment operations (`ap-southeast-2`) |
| `AWS_CLUSTER_NAME_HQ` | Backend | Target ECS Fargate cluster name (`microps-tenant-cluster`) |
| `ECS_EXECUTION_ROLE_ARN`| Backend | IAM Role ARN for ECS task execution |
| `ECS_TASK_ROLE_ARN` | Backend | IAM Role ARN for running ECS containers |
| `ECS_SUBNET_1` / `2` | Backend | Subnet IDs for placing tenant tasks |
| `ECS_SECURITY_GROUP` | Backend | Security group assigned to tenant containers |
| `ALB_ARN` / `ALB_DNS_NAME`| Backend | Application Load Balancer listener for routing tenant domains |
| `BASE_DOMAIN` | Backend | Root domain (`microps.in` in prod, `localhost` in dev) |

