## 8. Architecture Fixes & Local-to-Production Hardening

During production verification, three critical architectural refinements were incorporated into the core codebase:
1. **Unified Reverse Proxy Routing**: Client-side API requests (`ApiClientFrontend`) and real-time EventSource telemetry (`Dashboard.tsx`) route through an Nginx reverse proxy on port `80` pointing to PM2 cluster port `8000`, eliminating cross-origin resource sharing (CORS) friction.
2. **Dynamic Environment Telemetry Resolution**: Hardcoded localhost API references in React pages were refactored to consume `export const BASE_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL || 'http://13.238.226.195/api/v1'`, guaranteeing seamless SSE build stream connectivity across production environments.
3. **Queue Concurrency & Deduping**: BullMQ Redis queues (`tenant-builds`) strictly enforce single PM2 daemon processing, preventing stale container worker collisions during build orchestration.

